qas.question: How many times did Bohemian waxwings come to Britain in the nineteeth century?

Bohemian waxwings Bombycilla garrulus well show this unpredictable variation in annual numbers, with <a1_0>five<a1_0/> major arrivals in Britain during the nineteenth century, but <a2_0>18<a2_0/> between the years 1937 and 2000. Red crossbills Loxia curvirostra too are irruptive, with widespread invasions across England noted in <a3_0>1251, 1593, 1757, and 1791<a3_0/>.
